page.title: 09EVENTS IN GREAT HORKESLEY
page.content:
AFTERNOON WI AND YOUTH CLUB
AFTERNOON WI-ABOUT FORTY MEMBERS ATTENDED THE MONTHLY MEETING ON JUNE 19,WHEN MR.D.BARETT GAVE A TALK ABOUT THE MARY ROSE,WELL ILLUSTRATED WITH SLIDES.HE ALSO SPOKE ABOUT HIS PERSONAL DIVING EXPERIENCES IN ISRAEL. MRS WORMAN THANKED HIM.THE COMPETITION OF THE MONTH WAS AN INTERESTING OLD CARD,AND MRS GRIFFENS ENTRY WAS FIRST,WITH MRS LORRIMERS SECOND,AND MRS MCLENNAN THIRD.THE REDECORATION OF THE HALL WAS NOW FINISHED,AND MRS LORRIMER EXPRESSED THEIR GREAT APPRECIATION OF THE WORK DONE BY THE TEAM UNDER THE COMMUNITY PROGRAMME
YOUTH CLUB-THE IMMINENT CLOSURE OF THE CLUB WAS RECENTLY ANNOUNCED,DUE TO THE DEPARTURE FROM THE VILLAGE OF MR BARRY HART,THE CURRENT CLUB LEADER.
